do_not_schedule.description: Hard exclude — provider is completely skipped by all engines, validation, and analysis.
do_not_schedule.rule_format: Free text (reason). Engine only checks for tag presence, ignores rule content.
do_not_schedule.notes: Use for providers on extended leave, terminated, or otherwise unavailable for the entire block.

no_elmer.description: Removes Elmer from this provider's eligible sites.
no_elmer.rule_format: Free text (reason). Engine only checks for tag presence.
no_elmer.notes: If rule mentions additional restrictions (e.g., 'only Vineland'), those are NOT enforced by this tag. Use additional tags or adjust pct columns.

no_vineland.description: Removes Vineland from this provider's eligible sites.
no_vineland.rule_format: Free text (reason). Engine only checks for tag presence.
no_vineland.notes: Same as no_elmer — only the site removal is enforced. Other constraints in the rule text are not parsed.

days_per_week.description: Overrides the default 5-day divisor for week calculations. Used in capacity checks and stretch risk.
days_per_week.rule_format: Tag name must include the value: 'days_per_week: N'. Rule field is free text (reason).
days_per_week.notes: Non-standard: the value is embedded in the tag name, not the rule. Tag name must be exactly 'days_per_week: N' where N is the number of days.

swing_shift.description: Marks provider as having a day/swing split. Bumps stretch risk one level due to compressed day schedule.
swing_shift.rule_format: Free text describing the split breakdown.
swing_shift.notes: Rule text is informational — engine only checks for tag presence. The actual shift counts come from the Providers tab.

pa_rotation.description: Marks provider as having PA (physician assistant supervision) weeks. Reduces effective clinical density in stretch risk.
pa_rotation.rule_format: Free text describing the PA allocation.
pa_rotation.notes: Engine checks for tag presence and parses week count from rule text where possible.

pct_override.description: Overrides annual site percentage targets for the current block. Used in Check 3 (site distribution validation).
pct_override.rule_format: Comma-separated site:value pairs. Sites matched fuzzy. Values are percentages (with or without %).
pct_override.notes: Site names are fuzzy-matched (e.g., 'mh' → Mullica Hill, 'veb' → Vineland/Elmer). Values should sum to ~100%.

location_restriction.description: Restricts provider to specific sites. More flexible than no_elmer/no_vineland.
location_restriction.rule_format: To be defined. Proposed: comma-separated list of allowed sites, OR 'only: site1, site2' / 'exclude: site1, site2'.
location_restriction.notes: Currently not enforced. 6 providers have this tag. Could be enforced by filtering eligible sites.

scheduling_priority.description: Defines the order in which this provider's assignments should be made.
scheduling_priority.rule_format: To be defined. Proposed: comma-separated ordered list of assignment types/sites.
scheduling_priority.example: Schedule nights first, then Cape, then Cooper
scheduling_priority.notes: Currently not enforced. 5 providers have this. Would need engine support for phased per-provider assignment.

night_constraint.description: Constraints on night shift assignments — no nights, specific night limits, day-of-week restrictions.
night_constraint.rule_format: To be defined. Will depend on night scheduling architecture.
night_constraint.notes: Currently not enforced. 7 providers have this. Will be needed when night scheduling is built.

service_restriction.description: Teaching vs non-teaching service splits within a site.
service_restriction.rule_format: To be defined. Will depend on service-level assignment architecture.
service_restriction.notes: Currently not enforced. 2 providers have this. Engine currently assigns to sites, not services.

split_department.description: Provider splits time between IM and another department (e.g., Peds). IM allocation should be reduced accordingly.
split_department.rule_format: To be defined. Proposed: 'department: N weeks, N weekends'.
split_department.example: Peds 0.35: 10 weeks and 4 weekends per year
split_department.notes: Currently not enforced. 2 providers have this. Providers tab annual_weeks may or may not already reflect the split — needs confirmation.

protected_time.description: Provider has reduced allocation due to protected/admin time.
protected_time.rule_format: To be defined. Proposed: 'N weeks, N weekends' or reference to Providers tab.
protected_time.notes: Currently not enforced. 1 provider has this. Providers tab annual_weeks may already reflect this — needs confirmation.

no_um.description: Provider cannot be assigned UM (utilization management) shifts.
no_um.rule_format: Free text. Engine checks for tag presence only.
no_um.notes: Currently not enforced. 1 provider has this. Service-level constraint — depends on service assignment being built.

fmla.description: Records FMLA/leave history. Informational reference for the scheduler.
fmla.rule_format: Structured text: 'LeaveBegDate: YYYY-MM-DD; LeaveEndDate: YYYY-MM-DD; Reason-Relationship: text; Return to work: YYYY-MM-DD'
fmla.example: LeaveBegDate: 2025-04-29; LeaveEndDate: 2025-06-15; Reason-Relationship: ADA Accommodation Leave; Return to work: 2025-06-16
fmla.notes: Engine does not read this. Leave periods should be reflected in availability JSONs or do_not_schedule tags. Kept as audit trail.

note.description: General human-readable note. The engine does not read or act on this.
note.notes: Catch-all for information that doesn't fit another tag. If a note describes an enforceable constraint, consider converting it to a proper typed tag.
